### TelemetryDemo — Manual Test Requests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension (ms-vscode.rest-client)
### or copy the curl commands from the comments below.
###
### These requests exercise ALL telemetry metrics:
###   mcp.tool.invocations  ← calls to tools/call
###   mcp.tool.duration     ← measured for every tool/call
###   mcp.tool.errors       ← AlwaysFails tool
###   mcp.prompt.requests   ← prompts/get
###   mcp.resource.reads    ← resources/read

@host = http://localhost:5000

# ─── Step 0: Initialize the MCP session ───────────────────────
# ALWAYS run this first. MCP requires an initialize handshake.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 0,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client-test", "version": "1.0" }
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 1: List all registered tools ────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {}
}

###

# ─── Step 2: METRIC: mcp.tool.invocations + mcp.tool.duration ─
# Calls the fast 'Greet' tool. Run multiple times to see counter grow.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "Greet",
    "arguments": { "name": "World" }
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 3: METRIC: mcp.tool.duration (large value) ──────────
# Calls the slow tool — generates a 1000ms+ duration data point.
# Watch dotnet-counters: mcp.tool.duration histogram should spike.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "SlowOperation",
    "arguments": { "delayMs": 1000 }
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 4: METRIC: mcp.tool.errors ─────────────────────────
# This tool always throws. The response will be a JSON-RPC error.
# Watch dotnet-counters: mcp.tool.errors counter should increment.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 4,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "AlwaysFails",
    "arguments": { "reason": "testing-error-metrics" }
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 5: METRIC: mcp.prompt.requests ─────────────────────
# Gets a prompt — increments the mcp.prompt.requests counter.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 5,
  "method": "prompts/get",
  "params": {
    "name": "analyze-metrics",
    "arguments": { "focus": "errors" }
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 6: METRIC: mcp.resource.reads ─────────────────────
# Reads the status resource — increments mcp.resource.reads.
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 6,
  "method": "resources/read",
  "params": {
    "uri": "telemetry://status"
  }
}

###

# ─── Step 7: Repeat Greet 5 times to see counter accumulate ───
POST {{host}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":7,"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"Greet","arguments":{"name":"Alice"}}}

